# Software Team – Inward & Outward Stock SOP

## 1. Purpose
This SOP defines the process for managing **inward and outward stock** (components, devices, products) in the Software Team to ensure proper tracking, accountability, and transparency between departments.

---

## 2. Scope
This SOP applies to:
- All Software Team members  
- All components or products received from other departments  
- All components or products issued to other departments  

---

## 3. Responsibility
| Role | Responsibility |
|----|----|
| Software Team Member | Register inward and outward stock entries |
| Project Manager / Manager | Approval and visibility of outward stock |
| Receiver Department | Proper use and timely return of items |

---

## 4. Inward Stock Procedure

### When to Use
When the Software Team receives **any component, device, or product** from another department.

### Steps
1. Receive the item from the respective department.
2. Verify the item condition and quantity.
3. Make an immediate entry in the **Inward Register**.
4. Store the item safely after registration.

### Inward Register Fields
- Date  
- Product / Component Name  
- Quantity  
- From Department Name  
- Purpose (Testing / Development / Support)  
- Received By (Name & Signature)

---

## 5. Outward Stock Procedure

### When to Use
When the Software Team issues **any component, device, or product** to another department.

### Mandatory Pre-Checks
- Confirm all **internal software tasks** related to the item are completed.
- Check if the item is required for **future testing**.
- If required → **Do not issue the item**.
- If not required → Proceed to outward process.

### Approval
- Inform the **Project Manager or Manager** before issuing any item.
- Outward items must be issued **only with PM/Manager knowledge**.

### Steps
1. Fill all required details in the **Outward Register**.
2. Get receiver confirmation and signature.
3. Issue the item only after register completion.
4. Track and follow up on the expected return date.

### Outward Register Fields
- Date  
- Product / Component Name  
- Quantity  
- Purpose  
- Receiver Department Name  
- Receiver Person Name  
- Expected Return Date  
- Receiver Signature  
- Issued By (Name & Signature)

---

## 6. Return & Verification
1. Verify the returned item’s quantity and physical condition.
2. Update the return status in the outward register.
3. Report any damage or missing items to the PM/Manager immediately.

---

## 7. Compliance
- No inward or outward movement without register entry.
- No outward issue without PM/Manager awareness.
- Non-compliance may lead to accountability actions.

---

## 8. Document Control
- Document Owner: Software Team  
- Version: 1.0  
- Effective Date: YYYY-MM-DD  
- Review Cycle: As required
